zhnVoice.description: This file defines the private Enterprise MIB extensions that define voice related objects supported by the Zhone VoIP CPEs.

VoiceProfileLineStateType.name: VoiceProfileLineStateType
VoiceProfileLineStateType.description: Voice Profile line state for all lines in a profile. Enumeration of: Disabled Quiescent Enabled

DTMFMethodValues.name: DTMFMethodValues
DTMFMethodValues.description: DTMF Method values. Enumeration of: InBand Rfc2833 SipInfo

HookFlashMethodValues.name: HookFlashMethodValues
HookFlashMethodValues.description: Hook Flash Method values. Enumeration of: None SipInfo

RegionValues.name: RegionValues
RegionValues.description: Region values. Enumeration of: AUS -- AUSTRALIA BEL -- BELGIUM BRA -- BRAZIL CHL -- CHILE CHN -- CHINA CZH -- CZECH DNK -- DENMARK ETS -- ETSI FIN -- FINLAND FRA -- FRANCE DEU -- GERMANY HUN -- HUNGARY IND -- INDIA ITA -- ITALY JPN -- JAPAN MEX -- MEXICO RUS -- RUSSIA NLD -- NETHERLANDS NZL -- NEW_ZEALAND USA -- NORTH_AMERICA U45 -- NORTH_AMERICA 45 Vrms Ringing U95 -- NORTH_AMERICA 95 Vrms Ringing ULS -- NORTH_AMERICA Long Stutter URS -- NORTH_AMERICA 95 Vrms Regular Stutter POL -- POLAND ESP -- SPAIN SWE -- SWEDEN NOR -- NORWAY CHE -- SWITZERLAND T57 -- TR57 GBR -- UK TWN -- TAIWAN UAE -- UNITED ARAB EMIRATES

VoiceTransportValues.name: VoiceTransportValues
VoiceTransportValues.description: Transport protocol to be used in connecting to the SIP server. Enumeration of: UDP TCP TLS SCTP

VoiceLineStatusValues.name: VoiceLineStatusValues
VoiceLineStatusValues.description: Current status of a voice line. Enumeration of: Up Initializing Registering Unregistering Error Testing Quiescent Disabled

VoiceLineCallStateValues.name: VoiceLineCallStateValues
VoiceLineCallStateValues.description: Current call state for a voice line. Enumeration of: Idle Calling Ringing Connecting InCall Hold Disconnecting

VoiceProfileAddressModes.name: VoiceProfileAddressModes
VoiceProfileAddressModes.description: MGCP Client Name addressing mode. Enumeration of: ip(1) ipBracketed(2) domainName(3)

voiceRegistrationUp.name: voiceRegistrationUp
voiceRegistrationUp.description: This notification is generated when the Voice Client has successfully registered with the configured Call Agent.

voiceRegistrationDown.name: voiceRegistrationDown
voiceRegistrationDown.description: This notification is generated when the Voice Client registration with the configured Call Agent fails.

voiceServiceTable.name: voiceServiceTable
voiceServiceTable.description: Table of voice services, including voice profiles, capabilities, and physical interfaces

voiceServiceEntry.name: voiceServiceEntry
voiceServiceEntry.description: Table of voice services including voice profiles, capabilities, and physical interfaces

voiceBoundIfName.name: voiceBoundIfName
voiceBoundIfName.description: Name of the network interface that the voice service should run on. For example, brvlan300.

voiceBoundIpAddr.name: voiceBoundIpAddr
voiceBoundIpAddr.description: IP address of the network interface that the bound interface is configured for.

maxProfileCount.name: maxProfileCount
maxProfileCount.description: Maximum total number of distinct voice profiles supported.

maxLineCount.name: maxLineCount
maxLineCount.description: Maximum total number of lines supported across all profiles. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

maxSessionsPerLine.name: maxSessionsPerLine
maxSessionsPerLine.description: Maximum number of voice sessions supported for any given line across all profiles. A value greater than one indicates support for CPE provided conference calling. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

maxSessionCount.name: maxSessionCount
maxSessionCount.description: Maximum total number of voice sessions supported across all lines and profiles. This might differ from MaxLineCount if each line can support more than one session for CPE provided conference calling. This value MAY be less than the product of maxLineCount and maxSessionsPerLine.

signalingProtocols.name: signalingProtocols
signalingProtocols.description: Comma-separated list of signaling protocols supported. Each item is an enumeration of: SIP MGCP MGCP-NCS H.248 H.323 Each entry MAY be appended with a version indicator in the form protocol/X.Y. For example: SIP/2.0

regions.name: regions
regions.description: Comma-separated list of geographic regions supported by the CPE. Each item in the list MUST be an alpha-2 (two-character alphabetic) country code as specified by ISO 3166. An empty list indicates that the CPE does not support region-based customization via the Region parameter in the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i} object.

rtcp.name: rtcp
rtcp.description: Support for RTCP. A true value indicates support for the object VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.RTP.RTCP. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

srtp.name: srtp
srtp.description: Support for SRTP. A true value indicates support for the object VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.RTP.SRTP. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

rtpRedundancy.name: rtpRedundancy
rtpRedundancy.description: Support for RTP payload redundancy as defined in RFC 2198. A true value indicates support for VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.RTP.Redundancy. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

dscpCoupled.name: dscpCoupled
dscpCoupled.description: A true value indicates that the CPE is constrained such that transmitted call control packets use the same DSCP marking as transmitted RTP packets. If the value is true, the CPE MUST NOT support the DSCPMark parameter for call control. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

ethernetTaggingCoupled.name: ethernetTaggingCoupled
ethernetTaggingCoupled.description: A true value indicates that the CPE is constrained such that transmitted call control packets use the same Ethernet tagging (VLAN ID Ethernet Priority) as transmitted RTP packets. If the value is true, the CPE MUST NOT support the VLANIDMark or EthernetPriorityMark parameters within a call control object (e.g., SIP, MGCP, or H323). This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

pstnSoftSwitchOver.name: pstnSoftSwitchOver
pstnSoftSwitchOver.description: A true value indicates the CPE is capable of supporting the PSO_Activate Facility Action, which allows a call to be switched to a PSTN FXO (Foreign eXchange Office) line. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

faxT38.name: faxT38
faxT38.description: Support for T.38 fax. A true value indicates support for the object VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.FaxT38. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

faxPassThrough.name: faxPassThrough
faxPassThrough.description: Support for fax pass-through. A true value indicates support for the parameter VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.FaxPassThrough. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

modemPassThrough.name: modemPassThrough
modemPassThrough.description: Support for modem pass-through. A true value indicates support for the parameter VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.ModemPassThrough. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

toneGeneration.name: toneGeneration
toneGeneration.description: Support for tone generation. A true value indicates support for the object VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.Tone. A true value also indicates that the ToneDescriptionsEditable, PatternBasedToneGeneration, and FileBasedToneGeneration parameters in this object are present. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

ringGeneration.name: ringGeneration
ringGeneration.description: Support for ring generation. A true value indicates support for control of ring generation via the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.Line.{i}.Ringer object. A true value also indicates that the RingDescriptionsEditable, PatternBasedRingGeneration, and FileBasedRingGeneration parameters in this object are present. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

digitMapCapabilities.name: digitMapCapabilities
digitMapCapabilities.description: Support for a configurable digit map string. A true value indicates full support for the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.DigitMap parameter.

numberingPlan.name: numberingPlan
numberingPlan.description: Support for a configurable numbering plan. A true value indicates support for a configurable numbering plan via the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}. NumberingPlan object. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

buttonMap.name: buttonMap
buttonMap.description: Support for a configurable button map. A true value indicates support for a configurable button map via the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.ButtonMap NumberingPlan object. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

voicePortTests.name: voicePortTests
voicePortTests.description: Support for remotely accessible voice-port tests. A true value indicates support for the VoiceService.{i}.PhyInterface.{i}.Tests object. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

capabilitiesSIPTable.name: capabilitiesSIPTable
capabilitiesSIPTable.description: Table of SIP-specific capabilities. Applicable only if SIP is among the list of supported protocols.

capabilitiesSIPEntry.name: capabilitiesSIPEntry
capabilitiesSIPEntry.description: Table of SIP-specific capabilities. Applicable only if SIP is among the list of supported protocols.

role.name: role
role.description: The role of this VoIP CPE. Enumeration of: UserAgent BackToBackUserAgents OutboundProxy. A single VoiceService instance MUST have only one role. If a device includes the capabilities for more than one role, each role MUST be represented as separate VoiceService instance.

extensionsSIP.name: extensionsSIP
extensionsSIP.description: Comma-separated list of SIP extension methods supported. SIP extension methods MUST be in the form of the method name in upper case. The list MAY include vendor-specific extensions, which MUST use the format defined in TR-106. Examples: REFER INFO X_EXAMPLE-COM_MyExt

transports.name: transports
transports.description: Comma-separated list of SIP transport protocols supported. Each entry is an enumeration of: UDP TCP TLS SCTP The list MAY include vendor-specific transports, which MUST use the format defined in TR-106

uriSchemes.name: uriSchemes
uriSchemes.description: Comma-separated list of URI schemes supported beyond the URI schemes required by the SIP specification. Each URI scheme is given by the URI prefix, without the colon separator. Example: tel, fax

eventSubscription.name: eventSubscription
eventSubscription.description: Support for SIP event subscription. A true value indicates support for the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.SIP.EventSubscribe and VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.Line.{i}.SIP.EventSubscribe.{i} objects.

responseMap.name: responseMap
responseMap.description: Support for SIP response map. A true value indicates support for the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.SIP.ResponseMap object. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

tlsKeyExchangeProtocols.name: tlsKeyExchangeProtocols
tlsKeyExchangeProtocols.description: Comma-separated list of authentication protocols supported for TLS transport. Each item listed is an enumeration of: RSA DSS The list MAY include vendor-specific protocols, which MUST use the format defined in TR-106. Support for this parameter is applicable only if the Transports parameter in this object includes the value TLS and the TLSEncryptionProtocols parameter in this object is present and non-empty and includes at least one value other than Null

capabilitiesMGCPTable.name: capabilitiesMGCPTable
capabilitiesMGCPTable.description: Table of MGCP-specific capabilities. Applicable only if MGCP is among the list of supported protocols.

capabilitiesMGCPEntry.name: capabilitiesMGCPEntry
capabilitiesMGCPEntry.description: Table of MGCP-specific capabilities. Applicable only if MGCP is among the list of supported protocols.

extensionsMGCP.name: extensionsMGCP
extensionsMGCP.description: Comma-separated list of MGCP extension methods supported. MGCP extension methods MUST be in the form of the method name in upper case. The list MAY include vendor-specific extensions, which MUST use the format defined in TR-106. Examples: REFER INFO X_EXAMPLE-COM_MyExt

capabilitiesCodecsTable.name: capabilitiesCodecsTable
capabilitiesCodecsTable.description: Table to describe the set of supported codecs. Each entry refers to a distinct combination of codec and bit rate. The table MUST include a distinct entry for each supported combination of these parameters. Applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

capabilitiesCodecsEntry.name: capabilitiesCodecsEntry
capabilitiesCodecsEntry.description: The Codecs Service table MUST include a distinct entry for each supported combination of these parameters.

codec.name: codec
codec.description: Identifier of the type of codec. Enumeration of: G.711MuLaw G.711ALaw G.726 G.729 G.729a G.729e G.728 G.723.1 G.722 G.722.1 G.722.2 GSM-FR GSM-HR GSM-EFR iLBC The parameter MAY instead be a vendor-specific codec, which MUST be in the format defined in TR-106. For example: X_EXAMPLE-COM_MyCodec

bitRate.name: bitRate
bitRate.description: Bit rate, in bits per second. The value MUST be among the values appropriate for the specified codec.

packetizationPeriod.name: packetizationPeriod
packetizationPeriod.description: Comma-separate list of supported packetization periods, in milliseconds, or continuous ranges of packetization periods. Ranges are indicated as a hyphen-separated pair of unsigned integers. Examples: 20 indicates a single discrete value 10, 20, 30 indicates a set of discrete values. 5-40 indicates a continuous inclusive range. 5-10, 20, 30 indicates a continuous range in addition to a set of discrete values. A range MUST only be indicated if all values within the range are supported.

silenceSuppression.name: silenceSuppression
silenceSuppression.description: Indicates support for silence suppression for this codec.

voiceProfileEntry.name: voiceProfileEntry
voiceProfileEntry.description: Object associated with a collection of voice lines with common characteristics. By default, a single VoiceProfile object SHOULD be present in a VoiceService, initially in the disabled state.

voiceProfileEnable.name: voiceProfileEnable
voiceProfileEnable.description: Enables or disables all lines in this profile, or places it into a quiescent state. Enumeration of: Disabled Quiescent Enabled On creation, a profile MUST be in the Disabled state. In the Quiescent state, in-progress sessions remain intact, but no new sessions are allowed. Support for the Quiescent state in a CPE is optional. If this parameter is set to Quiescent in a CPE that does not support the Quiescent state, it MUST treat it the same as the Disabled state.

voiceProfileReset.name: voiceProfileReset
voiceProfileReset.description: When written as true, forces the all lines in this profile to be reset, causing it to re-initialize and perform all start-up actions such as registration. Always False when read.

voiceProfileNumberOfLines.name: voiceProfileNumberOfLines
voiceProfileNumberOfLines.description: Number of instances of Line within this VoiceProfile. Applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

voiceProfileName.name: voiceProfileName
voiceProfileName.description: Human-readable string to identify the profile instance.

voiceProfileSignalingProtocol.name: voiceProfileSignalingProtocol
voiceProfileSignalingProtocol.description: The protocol to be used for this profile. A single protocol selected from among the available protocols indicated in VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.SignalingProtocols.

voiceProfileMaxSessions.name: voiceProfileMaxSessions
voiceProfileMaxSessions.description: Limit on the number of simultaneous voice sessions across all lines in this profile. Must be less than or equal to VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.MaxSessionCount. (This MAY be greater than the number of lines if each line can support more than one session, for example for CPE provided conference calling.)

voiceProfileDtmfMethod.name: voiceProfileDtmfMethod
voiceProfileDtmfMethod.description: Method by which DTMF digits MUST be passed. Enumeration of: InBand RFC2833 SIPInfo If the parameter dtmfMethodG711 is non-empty, then this parameter applies only when the current codec is not G.711. The value SIPInfo is applicable only if the SignalingProtocol is SIP. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

voiceProfileDtmfMethodG711.name: voiceProfileDtmfMethodG711
voiceProfileDtmfMethodG711.description: Method by which DTMF digits MUST be passed if the current codec is G.711. Enumeration of: InBand RFC2833 SIPInfo An empty value for this parameter indicates that the value of the dtmfMethod parameter is to apply whether or not the current codec is G.711. The value SIPInfo is applicable only if the SignalingProtocol is SIP. This parameter is applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

voiceProfileHookFlashMethod.name: voiceProfileHookFlashMethod
voiceProfileHookFlashMethod.description: This object specifies which hookflash relay method to use. A value of None implies hook flash will be handled locally. A value of SIPInfo implies the hook flash will be sent via the SIP info.

voiceProfileRegion.name: voiceProfileRegion
voiceProfileRegion.description: The geographic region associated with this profile. This MAY be used by the CPE to customize localization settings. The value MUST be either one value selected from among the available regions indicated in VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Regions, or MAY be empty. An empty value indicates that the region is unspecified and the CPE SHOULD use default localization settings. This parameter is applicable only if VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Regions is non-empty.

voiceProfileDigitMap.name: voiceProfileDigitMap
voiceProfileDigitMap.description: Digit map controlling the transmission of dialed digit information. The string defines the criteria to be met as digits are collected before an outgoing request (e.g., a SIP INVITE) can be initiated. The syntax of this parameter is exactly the syntax used by MGCP as defined in RFC3435, section 2.1.5. This parameter is applicable only if the device supports a dialing mechanism for which a dialing plan is needed (for example, a device with an explicit Dial button may not need to be aware of the dialing plan) and if the device does not already support a dialing plan mechanism for this profile (e.g. in-band via MGCP). If this object is supported, the capability VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.DigitMap MUST be equal to true. Applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

voiceProfileDigitMapEnable.name: voiceProfileDigitMapEnable
voiceProfileDigitMapEnable.description: Enables the use of the DigitMap parameter in this object. When enabled, the content of the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.NumberingPlan object, if present, MUST be ignored. This parameter is required if and only if both the digitMap object and the VoiceService.{i}.VoiceProfile.{i}.NumberingPlan object are present. Applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

voiceProfileStunEnable.name: voiceProfileStunEnable
voiceProfileStunEnable.description: Enable or disable use of STUN to allow operation through NAT. Note: enabling STUN is to be interpreted as enabling the use of STUN for discovery, not use as a keep-alive mechanism.

voiceProfileStunServer.name: voiceProfileStunServer
voiceProfileStunServer.description: Domain name or IP address of the STUN server.

voiceProfileLogServer.name: voiceProfileLogServer
voiceProfileLogServer.description: Domain name or IP address of the Log server.

voiceProfileSwitchType.name: voiceProfileSwitchType
voiceProfileSwitchType.description: Configure the VoIP Switch Type. Enumeration of: broadSoft(1), cirpack(2), genband(3), metaSwitch(4), nortel(5), networkOnly(6), taqua(7), softX3000(8), axtelCS2K(9), copperCom(10), openSer(11), utStarCom(12), ericsson(13), unknown(99)

voiceProfileServiceProviderTable.name: voiceProfileServiceProviderTable
voiceProfileServiceProviderTable.description: Table of voice profile service provider objects

voiceProfileServiceProviderEntry.name: voiceProfileServiceProviderEntry
voiceProfileServiceProviderEntry.description: Service provider objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileServiceProviderName.name: voiceProfileServiceProviderName
voiceProfileServiceProviderName.description: Human-readable string identifying the service provider.

voiceProfileSIPTable.name: voiceProfileSIPTable
voiceProfileSIPTable.description: Table of SIP objects for a specific voice profile

voiceProfileSIPEntry.name: voiceProfileSIPEntry
voiceProfileSIPEntry.description: SIP objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileSIPProxyServer.name: voiceProfileSIPProxyServer
voiceProfileSIPProxyServer.description: Host name or IP address of the SIP proxy server. All SIP signaling traffic MUST be sent to the host indicated by this parameter and the port indicated by the ProxyServerPort parameter unless OutboundProxy is non-empty or a different route was discovered during normal operations SIP routing operation. Regardless of which host the traffic gets sent to (the ProxyServer or the OutboundProxy), the value of this parameter MUST be used to derive the URI placed into the SIP Route header field of all requests originated by this end-point unless a different proxy host was discovered dynamically during normal SIP routing operations.

voiceProfileSIPProxyServerPort.name: voiceProfileSIPProxyServerPort
voiceProfileSIPProxyServerPort.description: Destination port to be used in connecting to the SIP server.

voiceProfileSIPProxyServerTransport.name: voiceProfileSIPProxyServerTransport
voiceProfileSIPProxyServerTransport.description: Transport protocol to be used in connecting to the SIP server. Must be chosen from among the transports supported, as indicated by VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.SIP.Transports. Enumeration of: UDP TCP TLS SCTP

voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServer.name: voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServer
voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServer.description: Host name or IP address of the SIP registrar server. If this parameter is empty, the CPE MUST obtain all of the registrar server configuration information, including host name or IP address, port, and transport protocol, from the corresponding Proxy Server parameters (ProxyServer, Proxy-ServerPort, and ProxyServerTransport), ignoring all of the registrar server parameters (Registrar-Server, RegistrarServerPort and RegistrarServer-Transport).

voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServerPort.name: voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServerPort
voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServerPort.description: Destination port to be used in connecting to the SIP registrar server. If the RegistrarServer parameter is empty, the CPE MUST obtain all of the registrar server configuration information, including host name or IP address, port, and transport protocol, from the corresponding ProxyServer parameters (Proxy-Server, ProxyServerPort, and ProxyServer- Transport), ignoring all of the registrar server parameters (RegistrarServer, RegistrarServerPort and RegistrarServerTransport).

voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServerTransport.name: voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServerTransport
voiceProfileSIPRegistrarServerTransport.description: Transport protocol to be used in connecting to the registrar server. Must be chosen from among the transports supported, as indicated by VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.SIP.Transports. Enumeration of: UDP TCP TLS SCTP If the RegistrarServer parameter is empty, the CPE MUST obtain all of the registrar server configuration information, including host name or IP address, port, and transport protocol, from the corresponding ProxyServer parameters (Proxy-Server, ProxyServerPort, and ProxyServer- Transport), ignoring all of the registrar server parameters (Registrar-Server, RegistrarServerPort and RegistrarServer-Transport).

voiceProfileSIPUserAgentDomain.name: voiceProfileSIPUserAgentDomain
voiceProfileSIPUserAgentDomain.description: CPE domain string. If empty, the CPE SHOULD se its IP address as the domain.

voiceProfileSIPUserAgentPort.name: voiceProfileSIPUserAgentPort
voiceProfileSIPUserAgentPort.description: Port used for incoming call control signaling.

voiceProfileSIPUserAgentTransport.name: voiceProfileSIPUserAgentTransport
voiceProfileSIPUserAgentTransport.description: Transport protocol to be used for incoming call control signaling. Must be chosen from among the transports supported, as indicated by VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.SIP.Transports. Enumeration of: UDP TCP TLS SCTP

voiceProfileSIPOutboundProxy.name: voiceProfileSIPOutboundProxy
voiceProfileSIPOutboundProxy.description: Host name or IP address of the outbound proxy. If a non-empty value is specified, the SIP endpoint MUST send all SIP traffic (requests and responses) to the host indicated by this parameter and the port indicated by the OutboundProxyPort parameter. This MUST be done regardless of the routes discovered using normal SIP operations, including use of Route headers initialized from Service-Route and Record-Route headers previously received. The OutboundProxy value is NOT used to generate the URI placed into the Route header of any requests.

voiceProfileSIPOutboundProxyPort.name: voiceProfileSIPOutboundProxyPort
voiceProfileSIPOutboundProxyPort.description: Destination port to be used in connecting to the outbound proxy. This parameter MUST be ignored unless the value of the OutboundProxy parameter in this object is non-empty.

voiceProfileSIPOrganization.name: voiceProfileSIPOrganization
voiceProfileSIPOrganization.description: Text string to be used in the Organization header.

voiceProfileSIPRegistrationPeriod.name: voiceProfileSIPRegistrationPeriod
voiceProfileSIPRegistrationPeriod.description: Period over which the user agent must periodically register, in seconds.

voiceProfileSIPRegisterExpires.name: voiceProfileSIPRegisterExpires
voiceProfileSIPRegisterExpires.description: Register request Expires header value, in seconds.

voiceProfileSIPDSCPMark.name: voiceProfileSIPDSCPMark
voiceProfileSIPDSCPMark.description: Diffserv code point to be used for outgoing SIP signaling packets.

voiceProfileSIPVLANIDMark.name: voiceProfileSIPVLANIDMark
voiceProfileSIPVLANIDMark.description: VLAN ID (as defined in 802.1Q) to be used for outgoing SIP signaling packets for this profile. A value of -1 indicates the default value is to be used. If either the VLANIDMark or EthernetPriorityMark are greater than zero, then the outgoing frames MUST be tagged. Otherwise, the outgoing frames MAY be tagged or untagged.

voiceProfileSIPEthernetPriorityMark.name: voiceProfileSIPEthernetPriorityMark
voiceProfileSIPEthernetPriorityMark.description: Ethernet priority code (as defined in 802.1D) to be used for outgoing SIP signaling packets for this profile. A value of -1 indicates the default value is to be used. If either the VLANIDMark or EthernetPriorityMark are greater than zero, then the outgoing frames MUST be tagged. Otherwise, the outgoing frames MAY be tagged or untagged.

voiceProfileSIPInterdigitTimeout.name: voiceProfileSIPInterdigitTimeout
voiceProfileSIPInterdigitTimeout.description: Interdigit timeout, in milliseconds. This the value that will be used for T in the dial string. Four Seconds is the default value before the dial string is considered complete. Fifteen seconds is the maximum.

voiceProfileSIPAddressMode.name: voiceProfileSIPAddressMode
voiceProfileSIPAddressMode.description: Configure the SIP Client Name addressing mode. An enumeration of: ip(1) ipBracketed(2) domainName(3) Ip and IpBracketed will cause the SIP Client name to be the Bound Interface IP address. Name will allow the user to input any text field, usually a Domain Name.

voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeTable.name: voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeTable
voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeTable.description: Table of SIP subscriber event objects for a specific voice profile

voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeEntry.name: voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeEntry
voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeEntry.description: SIP subscriber events objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeEvent.name: voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeEvent
voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeEvent.description: SIP event name to appear in the EVENT header of the SIP SUBSCRIBE request.

voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifier.name: voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifier
voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifier.description: Host name or IP address of the event notify server.

voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifierPor.name: voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifierPort
voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifierPor.description: Destination port to be used in connecting to the event notifier.

voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifierTra.name: voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifierTransport
voiceProfileSIPEventSubscribeNotifierTra.description: Transport protocol to be used in connecting to the registrar server. Must be chosen from among the transports supported, as indicated by VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.SIP.Transports. Enumeration of: UDP TCP TLS SCTP

voiceProfileMGCPTable.name: voiceProfileMGCPTable
voiceProfileMGCPTable.description: Table of MGCP objects for a specific voice profile

voiceProfileMGCPEntry.name: voiceProfileMGCPEntry
voiceProfileMGCPEntry.description: MGCP objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileMGCPCallAgent1.name: voiceProfileMGCPCallAgent1
voiceProfileMGCPCallAgent1.description: Host name or IP address of the main MGCP call agent.

voiceProfileMGCPUser.name: voiceProfileMGCPUser
voiceProfileMGCPUser.description: User string used in accessing the call agent.

voiceProfilePersistentNotify.name: voiceProfilePersistentNotify
voiceProfilePersistentNotify.description: This field directs the MGCP stack to notify the switch for every hd or hu event when in the RQNT is Q:LOOP.

voiceProfileMGCPAddressMode.name: voiceProfileMGCPAddressMode
voiceProfileMGCPAddressMode.description: Configure the MGCP Client Name addressing mode. An enumeration of: ip(1) ipBracketed(2) domainName(3) Ip and IpBracketed will cause the MGCP Client name to be the Bound Interface IP address. Name will allow the user to input any text field, usually a Domain Name.

voiceProfileRTPTable.name: voiceProfileRTPTable
voiceProfileRTPTable.description: Table of RTP objects for a specific voice profile

voiceProfileRTPEntry.name: voiceProfileRTPEntry
voiceProfileRTPEntry.description: RTP objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileRTPLocalPortMin.name: voiceProfileRTPLocalPortMin
voiceProfileRTPLocalPortMin.description: Base of port range to be used for incoming RTP streams for this profile.

voiceProfileRTPLocalPortMax.name: voiceProfileRTPLocalPortMax
voiceProfileRTPLocalPortMax.description: Top of port range to be used for incoming RTP streams for this profile.

voiceProfileRTPDSCPMark.name: voiceProfileRTPDSCPMark
voiceProfileRTPDSCPMark.description:
Diffserv code point to be used for outgoing RTP 
packets for this profile. It is RECOMMENDED that by default the DSCP for RTP traffic be set to the value to indicate EF traffic.

voiceProfileRTPTelephoneEventPayloadType.name: voiceProfileRTPTelephoneEventPayloadType
voiceProfileRTPTelephoneEventPayloadType.description: Payload type to be used for RTP telephone events. This parameter indicates the payload type to be used for DTMF events if RFC 2833 transmission of DTMF information is in use.

voiceProfileFaxT38Table.name: voiceProfileFaxT38Table
voiceProfileFaxT38Table.description: Table of Fax T.38 objects for a specific voice profile

voiceProfileFaxT38Entry.name: voiceProfileFaxT38Entry
voiceProfileFaxT38Entry.description: Fax T38 objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileFaxT38Enable.name: voiceProfileFaxT38Enable
voiceProfileFaxT38Enable.description: Enable or disable the use of T.38.

voiceProfileFaxT38BitRate.name: voiceProfileFaxT38BitRate
voiceProfileFaxT38BitRate.description: Maximum data rate for fax. Enumeration of the following values: 2400 4800 7200 9600 12000 14400 33600

voiceProfileFaxT38HighSpeedPacketRate.name: voiceProfileFaxT38HighSpeedPacketRate
voiceProfileFaxT38HighSpeedPacketRate.description: The rate at which high speed data will be sent across the network in milliseconds. Enumeration of the following values: 10 20 30 40

voiceProfileLineTable.name: voiceProfileLineTable
voiceProfileLineTable.description: Table of voice profile line objects

voiceProfileLineEntry.name: voiceProfileLineEntry
voiceProfileLineEntry.description: Object associated with a distinct voice line. Support for adding and removing lines is conditional on whether the CPE supports more than one line in total as indicated by VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.MaxLineCount. By default, on creation of a given VoiceProfile, a single Line object MUST be present, initially in the disabled state. Applicable only for a VoIP endpoint.

voiceProfileLineEnable.name: voiceProfileLineEnable
voiceProfileLineEnable.description: Enables or disables this line, or places it into a quiescent state. Enumeration of: Disabled Quiescent Enabled On creation, a line MUST be in the Disabled state. In the Quiescent state, in-progress sessions remain intact, but no new sessions are allowed. Support for the Quiescent state in a CPE is optional. If this parameter is set to Quiescent in a CPE that does not support the Quiescent state, it MUST treat it the same as the Disabled state (and indicate Disabled in the Status parameter).

voiceProfileLineDirectoryNumber.name: voiceProfileLineDirectoryNumber
voiceProfileLineDirectoryNumber.description: Directory number associated with this line. May be used to identify the line to the user. In case of H.323 signaling, this MUST be an E.164 number.

voiceProfileLineStatus.name: voiceProfileLineStatus
voiceProfileLineStatus.description: Indicates the status of this line. Enumeration of: Up Initializing Registering Unregistering Error Testing Quiescent Disabled

voiceProfileLineCallState.name: voiceProfileLineCallState
voiceProfileLineCallState.description: Indicates the call state for this line. Enumeration of: Idle Calling Ringing Connecting InCall Hold Disconnecting

voiceProfileLinePhyReferenceList.name: voiceProfileLinePhyReferenceList
voiceProfileLinePhyReferenceList.description: A comma separated list of Physical Interface Identifiers that this Line is associated with. Each item corresponds to the value of the InterfaceID paraeter in a particular instance of the VoiceService.{i}.PhyInterface.{i}. table.

voiceProfileLineCMAcntNum.name: voiceProfileLineCMAcntNum
voiceProfileLineCMAcntNum.description: Indicates the call manager account number associated with this line instance.

voiceProfileLineOnhook.name: voiceProfileLineOnhook
voiceProfileLineOnhook.description: State of phones Receiver. On Hook if True, OffHook if False.

voiceProfileLineRowStatus.name: voiceProfileLineRowStatus
voiceProfileLineRowStatus.description: The SNMP RowStatus of the current row.

voiceProfileLineSIPTable.name: voiceProfileLineSIPTable
voiceProfileLineSIPTable.description: Table of voice profile line SIP objects

voiceProfileLineSIPEntry.name: voiceProfileLineSIPEntry
voiceProfileLineSIPEntry.description: Line SIP objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileLineSIPAuthUserName.name: voiceProfileLineSIPAuthUserName
voiceProfileLineSIPAuthUserName.description: Username used to authenticate the connection to the server.

voiceProfileLineSIPAuthPassword.name: voiceProfileLineSIPAuthPassword
voiceProfileLineSIPAuthPassword.description: Password used to authenticate the connection to the server. When read, this parameter returns an empty string, regardless of the actual value.

voiceProfileLineSIPURI.name: voiceProfileLineSIPURI
voiceProfileLineSIPURI.description: URI by which the user agent will identify itself for this line. If empty, the actual URI used in the SIP signaling SHOULD be automatically formed by the CPE as sip:UserName

voiceProfileLineMGCPTable.name: voiceProfileLineMGCPTable
voiceProfileLineMGCPTable.description: Table of voice profile line MGCP objects

voiceProfileLineMGCPEntry.name: voiceProfileLineMGCPEntry
voiceProfileLineMGCPEntry.description: Line MGCP objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileLineMGCPLineName.name: voiceProfileLineMGCPLineName
voiceProfileLineMGCPLineName.description: Used to identify the line when using MGCP signaling. If empty, the CPE SHOULD use the default names aaln/1, etc.

voiceProfileLineProcessingTable.name: voiceProfileLineProcessingTable
voiceProfileLineProcessingTable.description: Table of voice profile line processing objects

voiceProfileLineProcessingEntry.name: voiceProfileLineProcessingEntry
voiceProfileLineProcessingEntry.description: Line Processing objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileLineTransmitGain.name: voiceProfileLineTransmitGain
voiceProfileLineTransmitGain.description: Gain in units of 0.1 dB to apply to the transmitted voice signal prior to encoding. This gain is a modifier of the default transmit-gain, which is unspecified.

voiceProfileLineReceiveGain.name: voiceProfileLineReceiveGain
voiceProfileLineReceiveGain.description: Gain in units of 0.1 dB to apply to the received voice signal after decoding. This gain is a modifier of the default receive-gain, which is unspecified.

voiceProfileLineEchoCancellationEnable.name: voiceProfileLineEchoCancellationEnable
voiceProfileLineEchoCancellationEnable.description: Enable or disable echo cancellation for this line.

voiceProfileLineEchoCancellationInUse.name: voiceProfileLineEchoCancellationInUse
voiceProfileLineEchoCancellationInUse.description: Indication of whether or not echo cancellation is currently in use for this line.

voiceProfileLineCodecTable.name: voiceProfileLineCodecTable
voiceProfileLineCodecTable.description: Table of voice profile CODEC objects, per line

voiceProfileLineCodecEntry.name: voiceProfileLineCodecEntry
voiceProfileLineCodecEntry.description: The Voice Line CODEC list MUST include a distinct entry for each supported combination of these parameters.

voiceProfileLineCodecIndex.name: voiceProfileLineCodecIndex
voiceProfileLineCodecIndex.description: Unique identifier for each entry in this table. The value MUST match that of the corresponding entry in the VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Codecs table.

voiceProfileLineCodecEntryID.name: voiceProfileLineCodecEntryID
voiceProfileLineCodecEntryID.description: Unique identifier for each entry in this table. The value MUST match that of the corresponding entry in the VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Codecs table.

voiceProfileLineCodec.name: voiceProfileLineCodec
voiceProfileLineCodec.description: Identifier of the codec type. The value MUST match that of the corresponding entry in the VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Codecs table.

voiceProfileLineCodecBitRate.name: voiceProfileLineCodecBitRate
voiceProfileLineCodecBitRate.description: Bit rate, in bits per second. The value MUST match that of the corresponding entry in the VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Codecs table.

voiceProfileLineCodecPacketizationPeriod.name: voiceProfileLineCodecPacketizationPeriod
voiceProfileLineCodecPacketizationPeriod.description: Comma-separate list of supported packetization periods, in milliseconds, or continuous ranges of packetization periods as defined in VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Codecs.PacketizationPeriod. The set of packetization periods may be restricted by modifying the value of this parameter to a more restricted set of values than is listed in VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Codecs.PacketizationPeriod. The CPE MUST ignore any values or portions of ranges outside of those specified in VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.Codecs.Packetization.Period.

voiceProfileLineCodecSilenceSuppression.name: voiceProfileLineCodecSilenceSuppression
voiceProfileLineCodecSilenceSuppression.description: Indicates support for silence suppression for this codec. If silence suppression is supported, it can be disabled for this codec/bit-rate by setting this parameter to false.

voiceProfileLineCodecEnable.name: voiceProfileLineCodecEnable
voiceProfileLineCodecEnable.description: Enable or disable the use of this combination of codec parameters.

voiceProfileLineCodecPriority.name: voiceProfileLineCodecPriority
voiceProfileLineCodecPriority.description: Indicates the priority for this combination of codec parameters, where 1 is the highest priority. Where the priority differs between entries in this table, the CPE SHOULD use the highest priority (lowest numbered) entry among those supported by the remote endpoint and consistent with the available bandwidth. Where the priorities are equal among multiple entries, the CPE MAY apply a local criterion for choosing among them.

voiceProfileLineCallingFeaturesTable.name: voiceProfileLineCallingFeaturesTable
voiceProfileLineCallingFeaturesTable.description: Table of voice calling features, per line

voiceProfileLineCallingFeaturesEntry.name: voiceProfileLineCallingFeaturesEntry
voiceProfileLineCallingFeaturesEntry.description: The list of voice line calling features supported.

voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallerIDEn.name: voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallerIDEnable
voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallerIDEn.description: Enable or disable the transmission of caller ID information on outgoing calls.

voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallerIDNa.name: voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallerIDName
voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallerIDNa.description: String used to identify the caller.

voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallWaitin.name: voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallWaitingEnable
voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureCallWaitin.description: Enable or disable call waiting in the endpoint.

voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureMaxSession.name: voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureMaxSessions
voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureMaxSession.description: Indicates the maximum number of simultaneous sessions that may be conferenced together by the endpoint. For example, to enable three way conferencing, set the value of this object to 2. This value SHOULD be less than the value of VoiceService.{i}.Capabilities.maxSessionsPerLine.

voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureMWIEnable.name: voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureMWIEnable
voiceProfileLineCallingFeatureMWIEnable.description: Enable or disable call waiting in the endpoint.

voiceProfileLineStatsTable.description: Table of voice profile line statistics objects

voiceProfileLineStatsEntry.description: Line statistics objects associated with a specific voice profile.

voiceProfileLineStatsPacketsSent.description: Total number of RTP Packets sent for this voice line.

voiceProfileLineStatsPacketsReceived.name: voiceProfileLineStatsPacketsReceived
voiceProfileLineStatsPacketsReceived.description: Total number of RTP Packets received for this voice line.

voiceProfileLineStatsBytesSent.name: voiceProfileLineStatsBytesSent
voiceProfileLineStatsBytesSent.description: Total number of RTP Bytes sent for this voice line.

voiceProfileLineStatsBytesReceived.name: voiceProfileLineStatsBytesReceived
voiceProfileLineStatsBytesReceived.description: Total number of RTP Bytes received for this voice line.

voiceProfileLineStatsPacketsLost.name: voiceProfileLineStatsPacketsLost
voiceProfileLineStatsPacketsLost.description: Total number of RTP Packets lost for this voice line.
